metadata.name: Willie's Nightmare Cash Grab #2
metadata.description:
Through extensive lobbying, Disney helped change copyright law through the Copyright Term Extension Act to keep Mickey's earliest incarnation, Steamboat Willie, out of the public domain for an extra 20 years. While copyright law often protects artists, it shouldn't last forever. Thankfully, more hybridized forms of protection such as Creative Commons licenses have emerged allowing for protection as well as remixes and reimaginations. 

With Steamboat Willie now in the public domain, this collection builds upon Willie (and Disney's) nightmare of all sorts of off-brand chaos inflicted upon his form, transforming Mickey from an icon of family-friendly magic to one of nightmarish capitalism, sexual freedom, and murder run rampant. 

No commentary on the clash of capitalism and art would be complete without making this an open edition with a treasure hunt of trait pairings. The hunt will last as long as the open edition (two weeks), and after that, prizes shall be airdropped. 

For more information and to claim prizes, please join the House of Mors Discord: https://discord.gg/3N2KBfUuAN

Thanks to PureSpider for the image composition tool.

metadata.name: (fx)moji #124
metadata.description:
Emoji is the word for visual language, a way to express emotion without words.

From its humble origins as a Japanese emoticon in the mid-1990s, they exploded in popularity when appeared as a critical part of Apple's iPhone launch in 2007. The internationalization of emoji is an inexorable force, and today it is almost impossible to send a message without using one.

Emojis evolved as a way to communicate quickly and easily, and now they will evolve one more time and become an NFT generative art reborn as (fx)moji where basic geometric forms create a new full set of emojis expressions.

32 emojis,
7 Animations,
6 Color &
Infinite expressions 😊

Made with love ❤️ 🧡 💛 💚 💙 and p5js

metadata.name: Pixel skull #8
metadata.description:
The pixel skull is a Random Generated 10 PFP NFT.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 25 by 25 pixels and then resized to 1024 by 1024 resolution.
The number of Traits in this collection is 5 (59 layers) and it has the ability to make 38,688‬ different skull.

The percentage of some features has been reduced to create more special NFTs.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

metadata.name: Acequia #14
metadata.description:
Acequia (“ah-seh-kee-uh”) - a Spanish adaptation of the Arabic word as-sāqiya, meaning “water carrier”. 

In our second collaboration, Rich and Rick are back with our blend of generative code, intricate design, attention to detail, and a splash of charm. 

 Acequias are traditional irrigation canals used to distribute rainwater and snowmelt along a complex network of narrow channels. They are found in Spain, the American Southwest, and northern Mexico, where they are essential for sustaining fields, orchards, and gardens in semi-arid regions.   
Our aim in this series is to capture the essence of these waterways in bold geometric designs. Each piece is inspired by a mountain village or town in Andalusia (southern Spain). 

The location determines the cube designs and construction rules that are used to build the final output. These are combined with striking day/night palettes, outline styles, scales, climates, and a few surprises of course!


Controls (in live view): 

- Press [p] to pause water animation 
- Press [e] to complete water animation 
- Press [r] to reset water animation 
- Press [s] to save the current image 
- Press [h] for a high-res output suitable for printing 
- Press [b] to toggle the border

metadata.name: Neon Shadow #44
metadata.description:
A collection of geometric abstractions with architectural imagination.
